  "prompt": "\nConnect the resistor output pins (b) to the seven segment display segment pins. The components are:\n\n- R_A (id=354df611-5b81-4540-9eb3-25a731a9e723) pin b → Seven Segment (id=c6886597-972d-4b8e-baf7-9d041c6b183b) pin a\n- R_B (id=3a6fabc4-2147-41c2-9202-d69fff128f6f) pin b → Seven Segment pin b\n- R_C (id=cd9eed68-f0f1-4c0b-a8d8-b13fff978af6) pin b → Seven Segment pin c\n- R_D (id=6d29f5e9-a8f4-47b1-baa9-b5073953a14d) pin b → Seven Segment pin d\n- R_E (id=cffe5812-65de-40e3-bba1-8a4cb1a89f6e) pin b → Seven Segment pin e\n- R_F (id=1e3f7488-35f9-4bab-a995-7f3d693d8dcc) pin b → Seven Segment pin f\n- R_G (id=c664a44f-3a6e-4482-beae-3587d467933f) pin b → Seven Segment pin g\n\nAlso wire the Seven Segment common cathode (com/gnd) to Arduino GND (-3).\n\nUse yellow (#eab308) wires for resistor-to-segment connections.\n",
